    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The current military posture and activity patterns indicate a heightened state of alertness and readiness, particularly in the Middle East and Pacific regions. The deployment of USS Tripoli and USS Nimitz, as well as the replacement of USS Robert Smalls with USS Mustin, underscores a significant naval presence in these areas. The fire on board USS Gerald R. Ford raises concerns about the safety and operational readiness of the carrier strike group. Increased activity of Iranian forces in the Strait of Hormuz has heightened tension and vigilance among U.S. and allied naval vessels. The use of maritime drones in exercise Cobra Gold 2026 highlights the growing importance of unmanned systems in modern naval warfare. Additionally, strategic airlift missions and ISR activities are prominent, particularly in the Middle East and Europe, indicating a focus on monitoring and assessing threats. The presence of search and rescue missions in the Gulf of Mexico underscores ongoing efforts to ensure maritime safety and security. Overall, the intelligence summary suggests a complex and dynamic security environment, with multiple flashpoints and areas of concern that require close monitoring and analysis.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
